<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1440,381,950]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,568,381,405]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
Description. Male 
<typeStatus box="[440,562,381,405]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[667,760,381,405]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[847,939,381,405]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
; dorsal surface shiny except head slightly alutaceous. Color black; head yellow; pronotum with lateral 1/3 yellow; elytron with large, yellow, median macula joining macula on opposite elytron (
<figureCitation box="[722,808,445,469]" captionStart="Figures 35–49" captionStartId="23.[192,287,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[206,1434,320,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[192,1440,304,1704]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figures 35–49. Pentilia spp. 35-39) Pentilia jasmine. 35) Habitus. 36) Frons. 37) Penis guide ventral. 38) Penis guide lateral. 39) Penis. 40-44) Pentilia rachael. 40) Habitus. 41) Frons. 42) Penis guide ventral. 43) Penis guide lateral. 44) Spermathecal capsule. 45-49) Pentilia chelsea. 45) Habitus. 46) Frons. 47) Penis guide ventral. 48) Penis guide lateral. 49) Spermathecal capsule." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675051/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
); venter including abdomen yellow. Head punctures large, separated by less than a diameter; pronotal punctures small, separated by a diameter or less; elytral punctures as large as on pronotum, separated by 1–3 times a diameter, becoming larger, denser toward lateral margin; prosternum with small punctures separated by less than a diameter; mesosternum impunctate medially, small lateral punctures separated by less than diameter; metasternum nearly impunctate, with few, widely scattered punctures; abdominal ventrites 1, 2 with coarse punctures separated by less than to twice a diameter; ventrites 3–4 finely, densely punctured medially; ventrite 5 finely, densely punctured. Head with frons parallel sided, 1.5 times as wide as eye, clypeal apex widely emarginate, lateral angle abruptly curved (
<figureCitation box="[724,812,702,726]" captionStart="Figures 35–49" captionStartId="23.[192,287,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[206,1434,320,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[192,1440,304,1704]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figures 35–49. Pentilia spp. 35-39) Pentilia jasmine. 35) Habitus. 36) Frons. 37) Penis guide ventral. 38) Penis guide lateral. 39) Penis. 40-44) Pentilia rachael. 40) Habitus. 41) Frons. 42) Penis guide ventral. 43) Penis guide lateral. 44) Spermathecal capsule. 45-49) Pentilia chelsea. 45) Habitus. 46) Frons. 47) Penis guide ventral. 48) Penis guide lateral. 49) Spermathecal capsule." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675051/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
); eye canthus long, about 3/4 width of eye. Prosternum with lateral carina on each side short, straight, extended from apex of intercoxal process less than 1/2 distance to apex of prosternum. Epipleuron strongly descending externally. Postcoxal line on basal abdominal ventrite curved, extended slightly less than 1/2 distance to rear margin of ventrite. Genitalia with basal lobe as long as paramere, sides nearly parallel in median 7/8, narrowed to broadly rounded apex in apical 1/8; paramere slender, weakly curved, apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1177,862,887]" captionStart="Figures 35–49" captionStartId="23.[192,287,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[206,1434,320,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[192,1440,304,1704]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figures 35–49. Pentilia spp. 35-39) Pentilia jasmine. 35) Habitus. 36) Frons. 37) Penis guide ventral. 38) Penis guide lateral. 39) Penis. 40-44) Pentilia rachael. 40) Habitus. 41) Frons. 42) Penis guide ventral. 43) Penis guide lateral. 44) Spermathecal capsule. 45-49) Pentilia chelsea. 45) Habitus. 46) Frons. 47) Penis guide ventral. 48) Penis guide lateral. 49) Spermathecal capsule." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675051/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Fig. 47, 48</figureCitation>
); penis long, slender, apex attenuate, margins separated anterior to apex, lower margin curved; basal capsule slender, inner arm long, curved, apically rounded, outer arm as long as inner, apex rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1440,975,1031]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,300,975,999]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male except genitalia with ramus of spermathecal capsule bulbous, cornu slender, slightly curved, apex acute (
<figureCitation box="[536,624,1007,1031]" captionStart="Figures 35–49" captionStartId="23.[192,287,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[206,1434,320,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[192,1440,304,1704]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figures 35–49. Pentilia spp. 35-39) Pentilia jasmine. 35) Habitus. 36) Frons. 37) Penis guide ventral. 38) Penis guide lateral. 39) Penis. 40-44) Pentilia rachael. 40) Habitus. 41) Frons. 42) Penis guide ventral. 43) Penis guide lateral. 44) Spermathecal capsule. 45-49) Pentilia chelsea. 45) Habitus. 46) Frons. 47) Penis guide ventral. 48) Penis guide lateral. 49) Spermathecal capsule." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675051/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1440,1054,1143]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,331,1054,1078]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Variation.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[433,602,1055,1079]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.3">2.3 to 2.8 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[692,862,1055,1079]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.3">2.3 to 2.7 mm</quantity>
. Pale macula on elytron highly variable in size. It varies from that described above to a reduced spot completely surrounded by black surface of elytron with all intergrades present between extremes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
